# Performance Regression Baseline

- If the change touches performance-sensitive paths (hot loops, rendering, serialization, query logic, caching, networking), treat performance as a first-class requirement.
- Define a small perf sanity plan:
  - what to measure (latency, throughput, memory, query count, etc.),
  - what thresholds are acceptable,
  - how to compare before/after (or how to infer impact if no baseline exists).
- Prefer running any configured perf checks via placeholders:
  - `PERF_TEST_COMMAND`
  - `BUNDLE_SIZE_CHECK_COMMAND`
  - `LOAD_TEST_COMMAND` (if applicable)
- If no perf placeholders are configured, document why the change is unlikely to regress performance and what manual checks will be used instead.

